This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it presents a language model that develops syntactic structure and uses it to extract meaningful information from the word history. Additionally, the paper discusses the probabilistic parametrization of the model, which is a common approach in computational linguistics. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it presents a probabilistic model and evaluates its predictive power through experiments. 

The sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility because the paper presents a model that can extract meaningful information from text, which is a common task in natural language processing and AI. 

The sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a possibility because the paper may use neural networks or other evolutionary algorithms to develop the language model. 

Finally, the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) is a possibility because the model may use visual information to develop the syntactic structure of the language.
